"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-adam-peaty-paris-olympics-2024-swimming-b1149052.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the search feature\", \"from\": 7, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"your consent\", \"from\": 35, \"to\": 47}, {\"ngram\": \"cookies\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"similar technologies\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"search\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our privacy policy\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 205}, {\"ngram\": \"more information\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics Adam Peatysaid a new relaxed mindset can serve him well after securing passage to this summer'sParis Olympicsby finishing first in his signature 100m breaststroke event on the first day of the British Championships in London.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999942093399425, \"rank\": 5.688049773266355e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adam Peatysaid\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 258}, {\"ngram\": \"a new relaxed mindset\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 280}, {\"ngram\": \"passage\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympicsby\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 355}, {\"ngram\": \"his signature\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 388}, {\"ngram\": \"breaststroke event\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"the first day\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 429}, {\"ngram\": \"the British Championships\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 458}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old touched the wall in 57.94 seconds in the evening's final - the fastest men's 100m breaststroke time in the world this year and an improvement on the 59.10 seconds it took him to win bronze at February'sWorld Championshipsin Doha.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"57.94 seconds\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 521}, {\"ngram\": \"breaststroke time\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"an improvement\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 629}, {\"ngram\": \"the 59.10 seconds\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 676}, {\"ngram\": \"February'sWorld Championshipsin Doha\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty, who still holds the world record of 56.88 seconds in the event, is now set to defend his back-to-back Olympic titles after securing a nomination in the British championships, one year after pulling out of the 2023 event to begin what became an extended mental health-motivated hiatus from the sport.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.749949200197598e-13, \"text\": \"British championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 724}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"56.88 seconds\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"back\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 827}, {\"ngram\": \"a nomination\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2023 event\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"an extended mental health-motivated hiatus\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty said afterwards: \\\"I am not fully back, I have still got a second!\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1032}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's always going to be my mindset, but I have got a healthy approach to it.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my mindset\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"a healthy approach\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few years ago, I'd have come out of there disappointed, I have come out with a 57(-second time) and been disappointed, I have come out with a 59 and been quite disappointed.\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 57(-second time\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have learned to appreciate the moments of greatness for myself, not even relative to the world.\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moments\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"greatness\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1452}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For me, that was a great swim, executed well - but the most promising thing is that I am finding peace in the water now, instead of anger and just fighting it, and trying to win like that.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1642, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a great swim\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"the most promising thing\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1529}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"anger\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am finding a new version of myself which I am really liking, and I think that's a version that can do really well at the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new version\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"a version\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most direct way of securing a Paris 2024 nomination this week is to finish first in the open finals of each individual event, provided athletes clock in at or under a specific time set by the newly-rebranded Aquatics GB, though nominations are still subject to an official rubber-stamp by the British Olympic Association.\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 2105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.529096389061123e-22, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2001, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9962839190542152, \"rank\": 0.0037299416589062725, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The most direct way\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"the open finals\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1883}, {\"ngram\": \"each individual event\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1908}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes clock\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1933}, {\"ngram\": \"a specific time\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"nominations\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"an official rubber-stamp\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty's family 'give up hope of reconciliation after Ramsay's wedding comment' Gordon Ramsay on how he kept Holly 'calm' at Adam Peaty wedding amid family feud Sara Davies: Adam Peaty and Holly Ramsay threw wedding of the century 20 years on, this cult fragrance brand is still ahead of the curve Peaty emerged from his afternoon heat with a time of 58.53, the only man of 64 entrants in the event's heats to touch the wall in under a minute, marking another significant step on a comeback journey for the five-time Olympic medallist.\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2107, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 2165, \"end\": 2171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.9905222565824555, \"rank\": 0.007316757568627478, \"text\": \"Ramsay\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbped